  "prompt": "Who were the leaders behind the Revolt of 1857?",
  "response": "The Revolt of 1857, also known as the Indian Rebellion or the Sepoy Mutiny, involved several notable leaders from different regions of India. Some of the key leaders were:\n\n1. Bahadur Shah Zafar\n- The last Mughal Emperor\n- Nominal leader of the rebellion in Delhi\n- Proclaimed as the leader of the anti-British movement\n\n2. Rani Lakshmibai of Jhansi\n- A prominent female leader of the rebellion\n- Fought against the British in Jhansi\n- Known for her courage and military skills\n\n3. Nana Sahib\n- Leader of the rebellion in Kanpur\n- Challenged British authority in the region\n- Sought to restore Maratha power\n\n4. Tantia Tope\n- Close associate of Nana Sahib\n- Led military operations against the British\n- Conducted guerrilla warfare\n\n5. Begum Hazrat Mahal\n- Leader of the revolt in Lucknow\n- Took charge after her husband, the Nawab of Awadh, was exiled\n- Fought against British forces\n\n6. Kunwar Singh\n- Leader of the rebellion in Bihar\n- A prominent zamindar (landlord)\n- Fought extensively against British forces\n\nThese leaders represented different regions and backgrounds but shared a common goal of challenging British colonial rule.",
